//file permissions and access modes...

3 file attributes in unix

1. owner/user
2. group
3. other

// to check permissions on a file

ls -l filename

=> permission are represented in groups of 3
=> read(r/4), write(w/2), execute(x/1){run file as a program...}

//representation

-owner%group%other
-UGO

2 types of file changing permissions
	-Absolute...with numbers... 
		chmod 777 (gives all permissions...)
		
	-symbolic
		chmod o+wx filename
		+(add permission) , - (minus,remove), = (assign)
		chmod u-r filename
		chmod g = rx filename 
